></div><div>14</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hXHDmp5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>15</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fCTPUBb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>16</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3YHGCWe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>17</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Q5EDpSk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>18</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JBzBeya.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>19</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UyjeXh8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>20</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Mg790xv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>21</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CZqIbZn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>22</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VqFZyWx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>23</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GZ1lNaw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/MMMvQxU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ngugi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My best buddy Steve crossed the rainbow bridge today</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1PtwNG8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lH7C1Ck.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Obligatory I hope this dies in user sub. I'm in a new state and still don't have a lot of friends and don't want to bother people with my heartbreak right now. And, I want to remember exactly what happened as best I can. I'm still in a haze.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tH398jO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is my buddy Steve (Steeb Steeb). 

16 years ago I rescued him as a kitten from a shelter in Southeast Kansas. When I went into the room, Steve immediately ran over to me, put his paw on my hand, and talked to me. He was always a very vocal cat. I always loved the name Steve. It was the name that was on his adoption certificate, but I probably would have called him that anyway. Right before I went in to find him, I had just heard the rhymnoceros song by flight of the Conchords. A year later he got a brother, Felix, who is doing quite well. 

When he was a kitten, he would sit on my shoulders and share wheat thins with me. The first time he saw a mouse in one of the apartments I used to live in, he thought it was a toy. He went to pat at it, it squeaked and moved, and he was so scared he peed and bolted with a small trail of pee behind him. 

My exploring buddy has been with me through some of the darkest times of my life. He is a hero cat that pulled me back from the brink, once upon a time. He has always been more like a puppy. He waits by the door approximately the time I get off work and usually sleeps by my head.

We had moved around in the Kansas area a bunch and he always loved car rides. 

In 2018, my family and I had gotten out of debt and by 2021 we purchased a home in Alaska. That summer we bought a camper, fixed it up modestly, and drove from Southeast Kansas to Anchorage. Steve was a champ and really loved camping along the way. 

A few months ago, he had started to develop ear polyps. A local vet said that this was fairly common, but may need surgery depending on the severity. At the time we did not have the money to provide the surgery. Last month, I took him back to the bed and was told that the growing polyps were not the only issue. He had severe arthritis and liver dysfunction. They could only offer to make him more comfortable and give me more time with him. The picture above is from when he got back from that appointment.

Today, I had no choice but to bring him to the vet again. The polyps had grown overnight so much that he could hardly see or breathe out of his right side. I brought Steve to the vet. He really loved the car ride. I brought Steve in the vet in a carrier, but immediately took him out. I finally broke down as I was signing the paperwork. A sweet old man behind me with a puppers offered condolences, as did all of the staff.

 At the time, my wife and son are back in Kansas to help with family stuff and were distraught that they could not say goodbye in person.

Fortunately, right before they were to administer the first shot, the nurse returned and said that there was a gas leak and we had to wait in our car until they could clear it. I had the chance to video chat with my family to say goodbye.

After a few minutes, we were allowed to go back into the room where Steve, who had been eating tons of treats, had a few more treats and received his shot. I held his paw and gave him butt scratches as he got more and more sleepy. His claws dug in and I think he knew I was there. He was too tired to purr.

The nurse returned and gave the final shots. One was a further sedative and the other was supposed to cease brain activity. His heart stops shortly after.

As he was falling asleep, I just repeated "I love you, my good Steeb Steeb." 

It still doesn't feel real. He's been a part of my life for so long and been so important to me. I'm still sitting on my couch expecting him to jump up behind me. I heard Felix in the other room and, without thinking, called for Steve. I started to cry again. I know it was the best thing for him, and he is no longer in pain.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EEgN8IR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7MAomry.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I am so lucky to have had so much time with my boys.

*Thank you, strangers of the internet, for your support and reminders that he was most loved. I appreciate it greatly</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1PtwNG8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[derekthecleric]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Unusual restaurant in Japan</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JTyvvc8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MyVBTl2.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JTyvvc8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MedicalScience]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Honestly, I'm crying, thank you sir!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xZeXfZR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cP7hE2l.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I had 10 more days of food/rent... Now I have about 30. I'm so very very thankful. His only advice? 

"Pay it forward". 

On the positive front, had an incredible second-round interview today, and I have 4 more (firsties) this week, all in my industry. But tomorrow, I'll hit the retail/restaurant/warehouse circuit again, handing out resumes. 

This kind soul's support means it's feasible I won't be homeless! *dance dance*

I don't mind if this dies, I just didn't know who else to tell! Love you all!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xZeXfZR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BananaForScaIe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>'Lofe of my life '</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BKdnWtK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zO2rfjQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BKdnWtK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Iullyiullyus]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Small dump while up to early</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/5ua1lLS</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6eHgHzX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VpVi1n9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3JVQO7K.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RWFzOx2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ee60AjG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2ze6EWh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tXW54nT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qMAbkQS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/F2wwAfS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zmWd3iO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rZTKrNJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><